The invention is herein described, by way of example only, with reference to the accompanying drawings, wherein:


FIG. 1 is an isometric view of a first embodiment of a clamping assembly, constructed and operative according to the teachings of the present invention, for an injection molding apparatus, the clamping assembly being shown in an open position;


FIG. 2 is an isometric view of the clamping assembly of FIG. 1 shown in a closed position;


FIG. 3 is an exploded isometric view of a bushing assembly from the clamping assembly of FIG. 1;


FIG. 4 is a cross-section taken through the bushing assembly of FIG. 3;


FIG. 5 is an end view of the clamping assembly of FIG. 1 taken from the side of the moving platen;


FIG. 6 is a schematic isometric view of an alternative bushing assembly for use in the clamping assembly of FIG. 1;


FIG. 7 is a schematic representation of an alternative clamping force drive mechanism for use in the clamping assembly of FIG. 1;


FIG. 8 is a schematic representation of an alternative opening and closing displacement drive mechanism for use in the clamping assembly of FIG. 1;


FIG. 9 is a schematic side view of a second embodiment of a clamping assembly, constructed and operative according to the teachings of the present invention;


FIG. 10 is a first isometric view of a third embodiment of a clamping assembly, constructed and operative according to the teachings of the present invention;


FIG. 11 is a second isometric view of the clamping assembly of FIG. 10; and


FIG. 12 is a longitudinal cross-sectional view through the clamping assembly of FIG. 11.
